\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. H. ledifolium} (L.) Miller,{\i  Gard. Dict.} ed. 8, no. 20 (1768) ({\i H. niloticum }(L.) Pers., non Moench; incl.{\i  H. lasiocarpum} Desf. ex Willk.). Villous-tomentose annual 10-60 cm, variable in habit and size of parts. Leaves 10-50 × 3-12 mm, elliptical to lanceolate or obovate, greenish above, greyish beneath, rarely greyish on both surfaces; stipules linear to lanceolate, about as long as the leaves. Cymes 3- to 13-flowered, scorpioid; pedicels erect, thickened. Sepals 6-10 mm, accrescent; petals shorter than the sepals, yellow, cuneate. Seeds foveolate, smooth or papillose. 2n = 20.{\i  Dry places. S. Europe.} Bu Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si.
