\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. H. sanguineum} (Lag.) Lag. ex Dunal in DC.,{\i  Prodr. }{\b 1}: 273 (1824) ({\i H. retrofractum} Pers.). Much-branched, glandular-hairy annual 2-10 cm; stems often purple-tinged. Lower leaves 10-20 × 8-10 mm, elliptical, obtuse, caducous; upper leaves oblong-lanceolate, persistent; stipules 1/3 as long as the leaves. Cymes lax, 3- to 6-flowered; pedicels stout, curved before anthesis, strongly deflexed in fruit. Sepals 7-8 mm; petals yellow, shorter than the sepals. Capsule glabrous.{\i  Portugal, Spain, Italy, Kriti}. Cr Hs It Lu.
